TravisCI (#333)

Buildkite is a personal expense for me. This adds Gestalt's CI to also run in Travis.

- Travis has issues with zombie processes so I cleaned up the janky ./run_integration_tests script to cleanly kill all processes.
- I've disabled the bundlesize check from Danger (cc @bishwei) as it uses Buildkite's artifact storage.
- I've cleaned up the greenkeeper-lockfile steps from Buildkite that I don't have to port them to Travis and they're also unused.

Removes integration tests (#439)

* Remove integration tests

We now expect that integration tests lie closer to the consuming
libraries. They're still _really_ important, however a lot of these
tests rely on the environment in which they're run. In particular,
Masonry's tests are highly dependent on the actual things you put
inside Masonry.

The tests themselves still exist internally within Pinterest so no
coverage is actually being lost. The upside is that we can
significantly simply the project setup here.

Internal: Add CSS variables CI checks (#1041)

Improves safety of our CSS variables.

We introduced a split CSS bundle for legacy and future CSS in #963 but this resulted in potential breakages:

    await duplicateVariablesDifferentValues();
    await noVarInLegacyCSS();

### Duplicate Variables with Different Values

We already saw this issue in #971 where the font-size variables for `Text` and `Heading` got overridden resulting in heading sizes to be the same as text sizes

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/127199/87101340-b4aabc00-c203-11ea-8b2a-2723a0cba707.png)

*Test*: change a color that appears multiple times in 1 location: 
```
--gestalt-colorGray100: #efefef;
```
to
```
--gestalt-colorGray100: #efefed;
```

![Screen Shot 2020-07-09 at 4 19 04 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/127199/87101365-c5f3c880-c203-11ea-8668-d2cb3a91be03.png)

### CSS Variables in legacy CSS

This will break in IE11 since the compiled CSS will still contain the `var()`. We can only use `:root` for now so it does get replaced in the legacy build.

*Test*: Add this to any file CSS file
```css
.textFieldTemp {
  --gestalt-colorGrad: #111;

  color: var(--gestalt-colorGrad);
}
```

![Screen Shot 2020-07-09 at 4 31 43 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/127199/87101356-c2604180-c203-11ea-9101-973dbf16a239.png)

message: Internal: Upgrade ssri and is-svg dependencies for security alerts (#1477)

Bump postcss from 7.0.32 to 8.2.10 (#1503)

Bumps [postcss](https://github.com/postcss/postcss) from 7.0.32 to 8.2.10.
- [Release notes](https://github.com/postcss/postcss/releases)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/postcss/postcss/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md)
- [Commits](https://github.com/postcss/postcss/compare/7.0.32...8.2.10)

Signed-off-by: dependabot[bot] <support@github.com>

Co-authored-by: dependabot[bot] <49699333+dependabot[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Internal: Upgrade `stylelint` dependency to obviate `trim` security vulnerability (#1504)
Internal: Add resolution to latest version of `lodash` (#1505)
Internal: bump resolved version of multicast-dns due to security concern for dns-packet (#1523)
Internal: Update browserslist dependency resolution (#1524)
Internal: replace deprecated `postcss-cssnext` with `postcss-preset-env` (#1538)
Internal: add resolution for vulnerable `ws` package (#1539)
Internal: add resolution for `normalize-url` to fix vulnerability (#1545)
Internal: add resolution for `trim-newlines` to fix vulnerability (#1546)
Internal: add resolution for `css-select` to fix `css-what` vulnerability (#1543)
Internal: add resolution for `glob-parent` to fix vulnerability (#1551)

ComboBox: new component (#1563)

* Scaffolding

* foundation ComboBox

amendments

further work

a11y corrections

final changes

* docs fix

* Unit tests

* addressed comments

adjustments

* deprecated badge in Tyepahead

* displayLabel

* final commits
